    "question_id" : 77002721,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For me, I couldn't find the JRE version 11 anywhere:</p>\n<pre><code>default@host:~ $ sudo apt-get update\nHit:1 https://download.docker.com/linux/debian bookworm InRelease\nHit:2 http://deb.debian.org/debian bookworm InRelease\nHit:3 http://archive.raspberrypi.com/debian bookworm InRelease\nHit:4 http://deb.debian.org/debian-security bookworm-security InRelease\nHit:5 http://deb.debian.org/debian bookworm-updates InRelease\nReading package lists... Done\ndefault@host:~ $ sudo apt install openjdk-11-jre\nReading package lists... Done\nBuilding dependency tree... Done\nReading state information... Done\nPackage openjdk-11-jre is not available, but is referred to by another package.\nThis may mean that the package is missing, has been obsoleted, or\nis only available from another source\n\nE: Package 'openjdk-11-jre' has no installation candidate\n\n</code></pre>\n<p>But then searching for just plain <code>jre</code> showed that (for some reason) jre11 wasn't available but jre17 was available:</p>\n<pre><code>default@host:~ $ apt search jre\nSorting... Done\nFull Text Search... Done\nandroid-platform-tools-base/oldstable,oldstable 2.2.2-4 all\n  base tools for developing applications for the Android system\n\ndefault-jre/oldstable 2:1.17-74 armhf\n  Standard Java or Java compatible Runtime\n\ndefault-jre-headless/oldstable 2:1.17-74 armhf\n  Standard Java or Java compatible Runtime (headless)\n\n[many more options after this]\n\nopenjdk-17-jre/oldstable,oldstable-security 17.0.16+8-1~deb12u1 arm64\n  OpenJDK Java runtime, using Hotspot JIT\n\nopenjdk-17-jre-headless/oldstable,oldstable-security 17.0.16+8-1~deb12u1 arm64\n  OpenJDK Java runtime, using Hotspot JIT (headless)\n\nopenjdk-17-jre-zero/oldstable,oldstable-security 17.0.16+8-1~deb12u1 arm64\n  Alternative JVM for OpenJDK, using Zero\n\n</code></pre>\n<p>I was able to successfully install the version 17 JRE using:</p>\n<pre><code>sudo apt-get install openjdk-17-jre --yes\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
